700790f-a.title: Bronx: Concord Avenue - 141st Street (East)
700790f-a.text:
Concord Ave. (left), east side, north from East 141st to East 142nd
Streets, showing the Lincoln Hospital.
1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Writers Project photo.

700791f-a.title: Bronx: Concord Avenue - 141st Street (East)
700791f-a.text:
Concord Ave., east side, north from East 141st to East 142nd Street, showing construction work in progress on a unit of Lincoln Hospital. The
construction work is being carried out by the W.P.A.
January 5, 1937.
Works Progress Administration.
City Wide Project photo.

700793f-a.title: Bronx: Concord Avenue - 141st Street (East)
700793f-a.text:
Concord Ave., east side, north from East 141st to East 142nd Streets, showing a unit of Lincoln Hospital being erected by the W.P.A.
January 5, 1937.
Works Progress Administration.
City Wide Project photo.
